==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mohammedan year
<hw>Mohammedan year</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>The year used by
Muslims, consisting of twelve lunar months without intercalation, so
that they retrograde through all the seasons in about 32⟦frac12⟧ years.
The Mohammedan era begins with the year 622 <sc>a. d.</sc>, the first
day of the Mohammedan year 1332 being Nov. 30, 1913, according to the
Gregorian calendar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mohawk</ent>⟦br⟧
